59#if !HAVE_RSA_SET0_KEY
60/* From OpenSSL 1.1.0 */
61static int
62RSA_set0_key(RSA *r, BIGNUM *n, BIGNUM *e, BIGNUM *d) {
63
64 /*
65 * If the fields n and e in r are NULL, the corresponding input
66 * parameters MUST be non-NULL for n and e. d may be
67 * left NULL (in case only the public key is used).
68 */
69 if ((r->n == NULL && n == NULL) || (r->e == NULL && e == NULL)) {
70 return 0;
71 }
72
73 if (n != NULL) {
74 BN_free(r->n);
75 r->n = n;
76 }
77 if (e != NULL) {
78 BN_free(r->e);
79 r->e = e;
80 }
81 if (d != NULL) {
82 BN_free(r->d);
83 r->d = d;
84 }
85
86 return 1;
87}
88
89static int
90RSA_set0_factors(RSA *r, BIGNUM *p, BIGNUM *q) {
91
92 /*
93 * If the fields p and q in r are NULL, the corresponding input
94 * parameters MUST be non-NULL.
95 */
96 if ((r->p == NULL && p == NULL) || (r->q == NULL && q == NULL)) {
97 return 0;
98 }
99
100 if (p != NULL) {
101 BN_free(r->p);
102 r->p = p;
103 }
104 if (q != NULL) {
105 BN_free(r->q);
106 r->q = q;
107 }
108
109 return 1;
110}
111
112static int
113RSA_set0_crt_params(RSA *r, BIGNUM *dmp1, BIGNUM *dmq1, BIGNUM *iqmp) {
114 /*
115 * If the fields dmp1, dmq1 and iqmp in r are NULL, the
116 * corresponding input parameters MUST be non-NULL.
117 */
118 if ((r->dmp1 == NULL && dmp1 == NULL) ||
119 (r->dmq1 == NULL && dmq1 == NULL) ||
120 (r->iqmp == NULL && iqmp == NULL))
121 {
122 return 0;
123 }
124
125 if (dmp1 != NULL) {
126 BN_free(r->dmp1);
127 r->dmp1 = dmp1;
128 }
129 if (dmq1 != NULL) {
130 BN_free(r->dmq1);
131 r->dmq1 = dmq1;
132 }
133 if (iqmp != NULL) {
134 BN_free(r->iqmp);
135 r->iqmp = iqmp;
136 }
137
138 return 1;
139}

141static void
142RSA_get0_key(const RSA *r,
143 const BIGNUM **n, const BIGNUM **e, const BIGNUM **d)
144{
145 if (n != NULL) {
146 *n = r->n;
147 }
148 if (e != NULL) {
149 *e = r->e;
150 }
151 if (d != NULL) {
152 *d = r->d;
153 }
154}
155
156static void
157RSA_get0_factors(const RSA *r, const BIGNUM **p, const BIGNUM **q) {
158 if (p != NULL) {
159 *p = r->p;
160 }
161 if (q != NULL) {
162 *q = r->q;
163 }
164}
165
166static void
167RSA_get0_crt_params(const RSA *r, const BIGNUM **dmp1, const BIGNUM **dmq1,
168 const BIGNUM **iqmp)
169{
170 if (dmp1 != NULL) {
171 *dmp1 = r->dmp1;
172 }
173 if (dmq1 != NULL) {
174 *dmq1 = r->dmq1;
175 }
176 if (iqmp != NULL) {
177 *iqmp = r->iqmp;
178 }
179}

181static int
182RSA_test_flags(const RSA *r, int flags) {
183 return (r->flags & flags);
184}

190static isc_result_t
191opensslrsa_createctx(dst_key_t *key, dst_context_t *dctx) {
192 EVP_MD_CTX *evp_md_ctx;
193 const EVP_MD *type = NULL;
194
195 UNUSED(key);
196 REQUIRE(dctx->key->key_alg == DST_ALG_RSASHA1 ||
197 dctx->key->key_alg == DST_ALG_NSEC3RSASHA1 ||
198 dctx->key->key_alg == DST_ALG_RSASHA256 ||
199 dctx->key->key_alg == DST_ALG_RSASHA512);
200
201 /*
202 * Reject incorrect RSA key lengths.
203 */
204 switch (dctx->key->key_alg) {
205 case DST_ALG_RSASHA1:
206 case DST_ALG_NSEC3RSASHA1:
207 /* From RFC 3110 */
208 if (dctx->key->key_size > 4096)
209 return (ISC_R_FAILURE);
210 break;
211 case DST_ALG_RSASHA256:
212 /* From RFC 5702 */
213 if ((dctx->key->key_size < 512) ||
214 (dctx->key->key_size > 4096))
215 return (ISC_R_FAILURE);
216 break;
217 case DST_ALG_RSASHA512:
218 /* From RFC 5702 */
219 if ((dctx->key->key_size < 1024) ||
220 (dctx->key->key_size > 4096))
221 return (ISC_R_FAILURE);
222 break;
223 default:
224 INSIST(0);
225 ISC_UNREACHABLE();
226 }
227
228 evp_md_ctx = EVP_MD_CTX_create();
229 if (evp_md_ctx == NULL)
230 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
231
232 switch (dctx->key->key_alg) {
233 case DST_ALG_RSASHA1:
234 case DST_ALG_NSEC3RSASHA1:
235 type = EVP_sha1(); /* SHA1 + RSA */
236 break;
237 case DST_ALG_RSASHA256:
238 type = EVP_sha256(); /* SHA256 + RSA */
239 break;
240 case DST_ALG_RSASHA512:
241 type = EVP_sha512();
242 break;
243 default:
244 INSIST(0);
245 ISC_UNREACHABLE();
246 }
247
248 if (!EVP_DigestInit_ex(evp_md_ctx, type, NULL)) {
249 EVP_MD_CTX_destroy(evp_md_ctx);
250 return (dst__openssl_toresult3(dctx->category,
251 "EVP_DigestInit_ex",
252 ISC_R_FAILURE));
253 }
254 dctx->ctxdata.evp_md_ctx = evp_md_ctx;
255
256 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
257}
258
259static void
260opensslrsa_destroyctx(dst_context_t *dctx) {
261 EVP_MD_CTX *evp_md_ctx = dctx->ctxdata.evp_md_ctx;
262
263 REQUIRE(dctx->key->key_alg == DST_ALG_RSASHA1 ||
264 dctx->key->key_alg == DST_ALG_NSEC3RSASHA1 ||
265 dctx->key->key_alg == DST_ALG_RSASHA256 ||
266 dctx->key->key_alg == DST_ALG_RSASHA512);
267
268 if (evp_md_ctx != NULL) {
269 EVP_MD_CTX_destroy(evp_md_ctx);
270 dctx->ctxdata.evp_md_ctx = NULL;
271 }
272}

274static isc_result_t
275opensslrsa_adddata(dst_context_t *dctx, const isc_region_t *data) {
276 EVP_MD_CTX *evp_md_ctx = dctx->ctxdata.evp_md_ctx;
277
278 REQUIRE(dctx->key->key_alg == DST_ALG_RSASHA1 ||
279 dctx->key->key_alg == DST_ALG_NSEC3RSASHA1 ||
280 dctx->key->key_alg == DST_ALG_RSASHA256 ||
281 dctx->key->key_alg == DST_ALG_RSASHA512);
282
283 if (!EVP_DigestUpdate(evp_md_ctx, data->base, data->length)) {
284 return (dst__openssl_toresult3(dctx->category,
285 "EVP_DigestUpdate",
286 ISC_R_FAILURE));
287 }
288 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
289}
290
291static isc_result_t
292opensslrsa_sign(dst_context_t *dctx, isc_buffer_t *sig) {
293 dst_key_t *key = dctx->key;
294 isc_region_t r;
295 unsigned int siglen = 0;
296 EVP_MD_CTX *evp_md_ctx = dctx->ctxdata.evp_md_ctx;
297 EVP_PKEY *pkey = key->keydata.pkey;
298
299 REQUIRE(dctx->key->key_alg == DST_ALG_RSASHA1 ||
300 dctx->key->key_alg == DST_ALG_NSEC3RSASHA1 ||
301 dctx->key->key_alg == DST_ALG_RSASHA256 ||
302 dctx->key->key_alg == DST_ALG_RSASHA512);
303
304 isc_buffer_availableregion(sig, &r);
305
306 if (r.length < (unsigned int) EVP_PKEY_size(pkey))
307 return (ISC_R_NOSPACE);
308
309 if (!EVP_SignFinal(evp_md_ctx, r.base, &siglen, pkey)) {
310 return (dst__openssl_toresult3(dctx->category,
311 "EVP_SignFinal",
312 ISC_R_FAILURE));
313 }
314
315 isc_buffer_add(sig, siglen);
316
317 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
318}
319
320static isc_result_t
321opensslrsa_verify2(dst_context_t *dctx, int maxbits, const isc_region_t *sig) {
322 dst_key_t *key = dctx->key;
323 int status = 0;
324 const BIGNUM *e = NULL;
325 EVP_MD_CTX *evp_md_ctx = dctx->ctxdata.evp_md_ctx;
326 EVP_PKEY *pkey = key->keydata.pkey;
327 RSA *rsa;
328 int bits;
329
330 REQUIRE(dctx->key->key_alg == DST_ALG_RSASHA1 ||
331 dctx->key->key_alg == DST_ALG_NSEC3RSASHA1 ||
332 dctx->key->key_alg == DST_ALG_RSASHA256 ||
333 dctx->key->key_alg == DST_ALG_RSASHA512);
334
335 rsa = EVP_PKEY_get1_RSA(pkey);
336 if (rsa == NULL)
337 return (dst__openssl_toresult(DST_R_OPENSSLFAILURE));
338 RSA_get0_key(rsa, NULL, &e, NULL);
339 bits = BN_num_bits(e);
340 RSA_free(rsa);
341 if (bits > maxbits && maxbits != 0)
342 return (DST_R_VERIFYFAILURE);
343
344 status = EVP_VerifyFinal(evp_md_ctx, sig->base, sig->length, pkey);
345 switch (status) {
346 case 1:
347 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
348 case 0:
349 return (dst__openssl_toresult(DST_R_VERIFYFAILURE));
350 default:
351 return (dst__openssl_toresult3(dctx->category,
352 "EVP_VerifyFinal",
353 DST_R_VERIFYFAILURE));
354 }
355}
356
357static isc_result_t
358opensslrsa_verify(dst_context_t *dctx, const isc_region_t *sig) {
359 return (opensslrsa_verify2(dctx, 0, sig));
360}

362static bool
363opensslrsa_compare(const dst_key_t *key1, const dst_key_t *key2) {
364 int status;
365 RSA *rsa1 = NULL, *rsa2 = NULL;
366 const BIGNUM *n1 = NULL, *n2 = NULL;
367 const BIGNUM *e1 = NULL, *e2 = NULL;
368 const BIGNUM *d1 = NULL, *d2 = NULL;
369 const BIGNUM *p1 = NULL, *p2 = NULL;
370 const BIGNUM *q1 = NULL, *q2 = NULL;
371 EVP_PKEY *pkey1, *pkey2;
372
373 pkey1 = key1->keydata.pkey;
374 pkey2 = key2->keydata.pkey;
375 /*
376 * The pkey reference will keep these around after
377 * the RSA_free() call.
378 */
379 if (pkey1 != NULL) {
380 rsa1 = EVP_PKEY_get1_RSA(pkey1);
381 RSA_free(rsa1);
382 }
383 if (pkey2 != NULL) {
384 rsa2 = EVP_PKEY_get1_RSA(pkey2);
385 RSA_free(rsa2);
386 }
387
388 if (rsa1 == NULL && rsa2 == NULL)
389 return (true);
390 else if (rsa1 == NULL || rsa2 == NULL)
391 return (false);
392
393 RSA_get0_key(rsa1, &n1, &e1, &d1);
394 RSA_get0_key(rsa2, &n2, &e2, &d2);
395 status = BN_cmp(n1, n2) || BN_cmp(e1, e2);
396
397 if (status != 0)
398 return (false);
399
400 if (RSA_test_flags(rsa1, RSA_FLAG_EXT_PKEY) != 0 ||
401 RSA_test_flags(rsa2, RSA_FLAG_EXT_PKEY) != 0) {
402 if (RSA_test_flags(rsa1, RSA_FLAG_EXT_PKEY) == 0 ||
403 RSA_test_flags(rsa2, RSA_FLAG_EXT_PKEY) == 0)
404 return (false);
405 /*
406 * Can't compare private parameters, BTW does it make sense?
407 */
408 return (true);
409 }
410
411 if (d1 != NULL || d2 != NULL) {
412 if (d1 == NULL || d2 == NULL)
413 return (false);
414 RSA_get0_factors(rsa1, &p1, &q1);
415 RSA_get0_factors(rsa2, &p2, &q2);
416 status = BN_cmp(d1, d2) || BN_cmp(p1, p1) || BN_cmp(q1, q2);
417
418 if (status != 0)
419 return (false);
420 }
421 return (true);
422}
423
424static int
425progress_cb(int p, int n, BN_GENCB *cb) {
426 union {
427 void *dptr;
428 void (*fptr)(int);
429 } u;
430
431 UNUSED(n);
432
433 u.dptr = BN_GENCB_get_arg(cb);
434 if (u.fptr != NULL)
435 u.fptr(p);
436 return (1);
437}

439static isc_result_t
440opensslrsa_generate(dst_key_t *key, int exp, void (*callback)(int)) {
441 isc_result_t ret = DST_R_OPENSSLFAILURE;
442 union {
443 void *dptr;
444 void (*fptr)(int);
445 } u;
446 RSA *rsa = RSA_new();
447 BIGNUM *e = BN_new();
448#if OPENSSL_VERSION_NUMBER < 0x10100000L || defined(LIBRESSL_VERSION_NUMBER)
449 BN_GENCB _cb;
450#endif
451 BN_GENCB *cb = BN_GENCB_new();
452 EVP_PKEY *pkey = EVP_PKEY_new();
453
454 /*
455 * Reject incorrect RSA key lengths.
456 */
457 switch (key->key_alg) {
458 case DST_ALG_RSASHA1:
459 case DST_ALG_NSEC3RSASHA1:
460 /* From RFC 3110 */
461 if (key->key_size > 4096)
462 goto err;
463 break;
464 case DST_ALG_RSASHA256:
465 /* From RFC 5702 */
466 if ((key->key_size < 512) ||
467 (key->key_size > 4096))
468 goto err;
469 break;
470 case DST_ALG_RSASHA512:
471 /* From RFC 5702 */
472 if ((key->key_size < 1024) ||
473 (key->key_size > 4096))
474 goto err;
475 break;
476 default:
477 INSIST(0);
478 ISC_UNREACHABLE();
479 }
480
481 if (rsa == NULL || e == NULL || cb == NULL)
482 goto err;
483 if (pkey == NULL)
484 goto err;
485 if (!EVP_PKEY_set1_RSA(pkey, rsa))
486 goto err;
487
488 if (exp == 0) {
489 /* RSA_F4 0x10001 */
490 BN_set_bit(e, 0);
491 BN_set_bit(e, 16);
492 } else {
493 /* (phased-out) F5 0x100000001 */
494 BN_set_bit(e, 0);
495 BN_set_bit(e, 32);
496 }
497
498 if (callback == NULL) {
499 BN_GENCB_set_old(cb, NULL, NULL);
500 } else {
501 u.fptr = callback;
502 BN_GENCB_set(cb, &progress_cb, u.dptr);
503 }
504
505 if (RSA_generate_key_ex(rsa, key->key_size, e, cb)) {
506 BN_free(e);
507 BN_GENCB_free(cb);
508 cb = NULL;
509 key->keydata.pkey = pkey;
510
511 RSA_free(rsa);
512 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
513 }
514 ret = dst__openssl_toresult2("RSA_generate_key_ex",
515 DST_R_OPENSSLFAILURE);
516
517 err:
518 if (pkey != NULL) {
519 EVP_PKEY_free(pkey);
520 pkey = NULL;
521 }
522 if (e != NULL) {
523 BN_free(e);
524 e = NULL;
525 }
526 if (rsa != NULL) {
527 RSA_free(rsa);
528 rsa = NULL;
529 }
530 if (cb != NULL) {
531 BN_GENCB_free(cb);
532 cb = NULL;
533 }
534 return (dst__openssl_toresult(ret));
535}
536
537static bool
538opensslrsa_isprivate(const dst_key_t *key) {
539 const BIGNUM *d = NULL;
540 RSA *rsa = EVP_PKEY_get1_RSA(key->keydata.pkey);
541 INSIST(rsa != NULL);
542 RSA_free(rsa);
543 /* key->keydata.pkey still has a reference so rsa is still valid. */
544 if (rsa != NULL && RSA_test_flags(rsa, RSA_FLAG_EXT_PKEY) != 0)
545 return (true);
546 RSA_get0_key(rsa, NULL, NULL, &d);
547 return (rsa != NULL && d != NULL);
548}
549
550static void
551opensslrsa_destroy(dst_key_t *key) {
552 EVP_PKEY *pkey = key->keydata.pkey;
553 EVP_PKEY_free(pkey);
554 key->keydata.pkey = NULL;
555}

557static isc_result_t
558opensslrsa_todns(const dst_key_t *key, isc_buffer_t *data) {
559 isc_region_t r;
560 unsigned int e_bytes;
561 unsigned int mod_bytes;
562 isc_result_t ret;
563 RSA *rsa;
564 EVP_PKEY *pkey;
565 const BIGNUM *e = NULL, *n = NULL;
566
567 REQUIRE(key->keydata.pkey != NULL);
568
569 pkey = key->keydata.pkey;
570 rsa = EVP_PKEY_get1_RSA(pkey);
571 if (rsa == NULL)
572 return (dst__openssl_toresult(DST_R_OPENSSLFAILURE));
573
574 isc_buffer_availableregion(data, &r);
575
576 RSA_get0_key(rsa, &n, &e, NULL);
577 mod_bytes = BN_num_bytes(n);
578 e_bytes = BN_num_bytes(e);
579
580 if (e_bytes < 256) { /*%< key exponent is <= 2040 bits */
581 if (r.length < 1)
582 DST_RET(ISC_R_NOSPACE);
583 isc_buffer_putuint8(data, (uint8_t) e_bytes);
584 isc_region_consume(&r, 1);
585 } else {
586 if (r.length < 3)
587 DST_RET(ISC_R_NOSPACE);
588 isc_buffer_putuint8(data, 0);
589 isc_buffer_putuint16(data, (uint16_t) e_bytes);
590 isc_region_consume(&r, 3);
591 }
592
593 if (r.length < e_bytes + mod_bytes)
594 DST_RET(ISC_R_NOSPACE);
595
596 RSA_get0_key(rsa, &n, &e, NULL);
597 BN_bn2bin(e, r.base);
598 isc_region_consume(&r, e_bytes);
599 BN_bn2bin(n, r.base);
600
601 isc_buffer_add(data, e_bytes + mod_bytes);
602
603 ret = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
604 err:
605 if (rsa != NULL)
606 RSA_free(rsa);
607 return (ret);
608}

610static isc_result_t
611opensslrsa_fromdns(dst_key_t *key, isc_buffer_t *data) {
612 RSA *rsa;
613 isc_region_t r;
614 unsigned int e_bytes;
615 unsigned int length;
616 EVP_PKEY *pkey;
617 BIGNUM *e = NULL, *n = NULL;
618
619 isc_buffer_remainingregion(data, &r);
620 if (r.length == 0)
621 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
622 length = r.length;
623
624 rsa = RSA_new();
625 if (rsa == NULL)
626 return (dst__openssl_toresult(ISC_R_NOMEMORY));
627
628 if (r.length < 1) {
629 RSA_free(rsa);
630 return (DST_R_INVALIDPUBLICKEY);
631 }
632 e_bytes = *r.base;
633 isc_region_consume(&r, 1);
634
635 if (e_bytes == 0) {
636 if (r.length < 2) {
637 RSA_free(rsa);
638 return (DST_R_INVALIDPUBLICKEY);
639 }
640 e_bytes = (*r.base) << 8;
641 isc_region_consume(&r, 1);
642 e_bytes += *r.base;
643 isc_region_consume(&r, 1);
644 }
645
646 if (r.length < e_bytes) {
647 RSA_free(rsa);
648 return (DST_R_INVALIDPUBLICKEY);
649 }
650 e = BN_bin2bn(r.base, e_bytes, NULL);
651 isc_region_consume(&r, e_bytes);
652 n = BN_bin2bn(r.base, r.length, NULL);
653 if (RSA_set0_key(rsa, n, e, NULL) == 0) {
654 if (n != NULL) BN_free(n);
655 if (e != NULL) BN_free(e);
656 RSA_free(rsa);
657 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
658 }
659 key->key_size = BN_num_bits(n);
660
661 isc_buffer_forward(data, length);
662
663 pkey = EVP_PKEY_new();
664 if (pkey == NULL) {
665 RSA_free(rsa);
666 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
667 }
668 if (!EVP_PKEY_set1_RSA(pkey, rsa)) {
669 EVP_PKEY_free(pkey);
670 RSA_free(rsa);
671 return (dst__openssl_toresult(DST_R_OPENSSLFAILURE));
672 }
673 key->keydata.pkey = pkey;
674 RSA_free(rsa);
675
676 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
677}

679static isc_result_t
680opensslrsa_tofile(const dst_key_t *key, const char *directory) {
681 int i;
682 RSA *rsa;
683 dst_private_t priv;
684 unsigned char *bufs[8];
685 isc_result_t result;
686 const BIGNUM *n = NULL, *e = NULL, *d = NULL;
687 const BIGNUM *p = NULL, *q = NULL;
688 const BIGNUM *dmp1 = NULL, *dmq1 = NULL, *iqmp = NULL;
689
690 if (key->keydata.pkey == NULL)
691 return (DST_R_NULLKEY);
692 rsa = EVP_PKEY_get1_RSA(key->keydata.pkey);
693 if (rsa == NULL)
694 return (dst__openssl_toresult(DST_R_OPENSSLFAILURE));
695 memset(bufs, 0, sizeof(bufs));
696
697 RSA_get0_key(rsa, &n, &e, &d);
698 RSA_get0_factors(rsa, &p, &q);
699 RSA_get0_crt_params(rsa, &dmp1, &dmq1, &iqmp);
700
701 if (key->external) {
702 priv.nelements = 0;
703 result = dst__privstruct_writefile(key, &priv, directory);
704 goto fail;
705 }
706
707 for (i = 0; i < 8; i++) {
708 bufs[i] = isc_mem_get(key->mctx, BN_num_bytes(n));
709 if (bufs[i] == NULL) {
710 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
711 goto fail;
712 }
713 }
714
715 i = 0;
716
717 priv.elements[i].tag = TAG_RSA_MODULUS;
718 priv.elements[i].length = BN_num_bytes(n);
719 BN_bn2bin(n, bufs[i]);
720 priv.elements[i].data = bufs[i];
721 i++;
722
723 priv.elements[i].tag = TAG_RSA_PUBLICEXPONENT;
724 priv.elements[i].length = BN_num_bytes(e);
725 BN_bn2bin(e, bufs[i]);
726 priv.elements[i].data = bufs[i];
727 i++;
728
729 if (d != NULL) {
730 priv.elements[i].tag = TAG_RSA_PRIVATEEXPONENT;
731 priv.elements[i].length = BN_num_bytes(d);
732 BN_bn2bin(d, bufs[i]);
733 priv.elements[i].data = bufs[i];
734 i++;
735 }
736
737 if (p != NULL) {
738 priv.elements[i].tag = TAG_RSA_PRIME1;
739 priv.elements[i].length = BN_num_bytes(p);
740 BN_bn2bin(p, bufs[i]);
741 priv.elements[i].data = bufs[i];
742 i++;
743 }
744
745 if (q != NULL) {
746 priv.elements[i].tag = TAG_RSA_PRIME2;
747 priv.elements[i].length = BN_num_bytes(q);
748 BN_bn2bin(q, bufs[i]);
749 priv.elements[i].data = bufs[i];
750 i++;
751 }
752
753 if (dmp1 != NULL) {
754 priv.elements[i].tag = TAG_RSA_EXPONENT1;
755 priv.elements[i].length = BN_num_bytes(dmp1);
756 BN_bn2bin(dmp1, bufs[i]);
757 priv.elements[i].data = bufs[i];
758 i++;
759 }
760
761 if (dmq1 != NULL) {
762 priv.elements[i].tag = TAG_RSA_EXPONENT2;
763 priv.elements[i].length = BN_num_bytes(dmq1);
764 BN_bn2bin(dmq1, bufs[i]);
765 priv.elements[i].data = bufs[i];
766 i++;
767 }
768
769 if (iqmp != NULL) {
770 priv.elements[i].tag = TAG_RSA_COEFFICIENT;
771 priv.elements[i].length = BN_num_bytes(iqmp);
772 BN_bn2bin(iqmp, bufs[i]);
773 priv.elements[i].data = bufs[i];
774 i++;
775 }
776
777 if (key->engine != NULL) {
778 priv.elements[i].tag = TAG_RSA_ENGINE;
779 priv.elements[i].length =
780 (unsigned short)strlen(key->engine) + 1;
781 priv.elements[i].data = (unsigned char *)key->engine;
782 i++;
783 }
784
785 if (key->label != NULL) {
786 priv.elements[i].tag = TAG_RSA_LABEL;
787 priv.elements[i].length =
788 (unsigned short)strlen(key->label) + 1;
789 priv.elements[i].data = (unsigned char *)key->label;
790 i++;
791 }
792
793
794 priv.nelements = i;
795 result = dst__privstruct_writefile(key, &priv, directory);
796 fail:
797 RSA_free(rsa);
798 for (i = 0; i < 8; i++) {
799 if (bufs[i] == NULL)
800 break;
801 isc_mem_put(key->mctx, bufs[i], BN_num_bytes(n));
802 }
803 return (result);
804}
805
806static isc_result_t
807rsa_check(RSA *rsa, RSA *pub) {
808 const BIGNUM *n1 = NULL, *n2 = NULL;
809 const BIGNUM *e1 = NULL, *e2 = NULL;
810 BIGNUM *n = NULL, *e = NULL;
811
812 /*
813 * Public parameters should be the same but if they are not set
814 * copy them from the public key.
815 */
816 RSA_get0_key(rsa, &n1, &e1, NULL);
817 if (pub != NULL) {
818 RSA_get0_key(pub, &n2, &e2, NULL);
819 if (n1 != NULL) {
820 if (BN_cmp(n1, n2) != 0)
821 return (DST_R_INVALIDPRIVATEKEY);
822 } else {
823 n = BN_dup(n2);
824 }
825 if (e1 != NULL) {
826 if (BN_cmp(e1, e2) != 0)
827 return (DST_R_INVALIDPRIVATEKEY);
828 } else {
829 e = BN_dup(e2);
830 }
831 if (RSA_set0_key(rsa, n, e, NULL) == 0) {
832 if (n != NULL)
833 BN_free(n);
834 if (e != NULL)
835 BN_free(e);
836 }
837 }
838 RSA_get0_key(rsa, &n1, &e1, NULL);
839 if (n1 == NULL || e1 == NULL)
840 return (DST_R_INVALIDPRIVATEKEY);
841 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
842}

844static isc_result_t
845opensslrsa_parse(dst_key_t *key, isc_lex_t *lexer, dst_key_t *pub) {
846 dst_private_t priv;
847 isc_result_t ret;
848 int i;
849 RSA *rsa = NULL, *pubrsa = NULL;
850#if !defined(OPENSSL_NO_ENGINE)
851 ENGINE *ep = NULL;
852 const BIGNUM *ex = NULL;
853#endif
854 isc_mem_t *mctx = key->mctx;
855 const char *engine = NULL, *label = NULL;
856 EVP_PKEY *pkey = NULL;
857 BIGNUM *n = NULL, *e = NULL, *d = NULL;
858 BIGNUM *p = NULL, *q = NULL;
859 BIGNUM *dmp1 = NULL, *dmq1 = NULL, *iqmp = NULL;
860
861 /* read private key file */
862 ret = dst__privstruct_parse(key, DST_ALG_RSA, lexer, mctx, &priv);
863 if (ret != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
864 goto err;
865
866 if (key->external) {
867 if (priv.nelements != 0)
868 DST_RET(DST_R_INVALIDPRIVATEKEY);
869 if (pub == NULL)
870 DST_RET(DST_R_INVALIDPRIVATEKEY);
871 key->keydata.pkey = pub->keydata.pkey;
872 pub->keydata.pkey = NULL;
873 key->key_size = pub->key_size;
874 dst__privstruct_free(&priv, mctx);
875 isc_safe_memwipe(&priv, sizeof(priv));
876 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
877 }
878
879 if (pub != NULL && pub->keydata.pkey != NULL)
880 pubrsa = EVP_PKEY_get1_RSA(pub->keydata.pkey);
881
882 for (i = 0; i < priv.nelements; i++) {
883 switch (priv.elements[i].tag) {
884 case TAG_RSA_ENGINE:
885 engine = (char *)priv.elements[i].data;
886 break;
887 case TAG_RSA_LABEL:
888 label = (char *)priv.elements[i].data;
889 break;
890 default:
891 break;
892 }
893 }
894
895 /*
896 * Is this key is stored in a HSM?
897 * See if we can fetch it.
898 */
899 if (label != NULL) {
900#if !defined(OPENSSL_NO_ENGINE)
901 if (engine == NULL)
902 DST_RET(DST_R_NOENGINE);
903 ep = dst__openssl_getengine(engine);
904 if (ep == NULL)
905 DST_RET(DST_R_NOENGINE);
906 pkey = ENGINE_load_private_key(ep, label, NULL, NULL);
907 if (pkey == NULL)
908 DST_RET(dst__openssl_toresult2(
909 "ENGINE_load_private_key",
910 ISC_R_NOTFOUND));
911 key->engine = isc_mem_strdup(key->mctx, engine);
912 if (key->engine == NULL)
913 DST_RET(ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
914 key->label = isc_mem_strdup(key->mctx, label);
915 if (key->label == NULL)
916 DST_RET(ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
917 rsa = EVP_PKEY_get1_RSA(pkey);
918 if (rsa == NULL)
919 DST_RET(dst__openssl_toresult(DST_R_OPENSSLFAILURE));
920 if (rsa_check(rsa, pubrsa) != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
921 DST_RET(DST_R_INVALIDPRIVATEKEY);
922 RSA_get0_key(rsa, NULL, &ex, NULL);
923 if (BN_num_bits(ex) > RSA_MAX_PUBEXP_BITS)
924 DST_RET(ISC_R_RANGE);
925 if (pubrsa != NULL)
926 RSA_free(pubrsa);
927 key->key_size = EVP_PKEY_bits(pkey);
928 key->keydata.pkey = pkey;
929 RSA_free(rsa);
930 dst__privstruct_free(&priv, mctx);
931 isc_safe_memwipe(&priv, sizeof(priv));
932 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
933#else
934 DST_RET(DST_R_NOENGINE);
935#endif
936 }
937
938 rsa = RSA_new();
939 if (rsa == NULL)
940 DST_RET(ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
941
942 pkey = EVP_PKEY_new();
943 if (pkey == NULL)
944 DST_RET(ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
945 if (!EVP_PKEY_set1_RSA(pkey, rsa))
946 DST_RET(ISC_R_FAILURE);
947 key->keydata.pkey = pkey;
948
949 for (i = 0; i < priv.nelements; i++) {
950 BIGNUM *bn;
951 switch (priv.elements[i].tag) {
952 case TAG_RSA_ENGINE:
953 continue;
954 case TAG_RSA_LABEL:
955 continue;
956 default:
957 bn = BN_bin2bn(priv.elements[i].data,
958 priv.elements[i].length, NULL);
959 if (bn == NULL)
960 DST_RET(ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
961 switch (priv.elements[i].tag) {
962 case TAG_RSA_MODULUS:
963 n = bn;
964 break;
965 case TAG_RSA_PUBLICEXPONENT:
966 e = bn;
967 break;
968 case TAG_RSA_PRIVATEEXPONENT:
969 d = bn;
970 break;
971 case TAG_RSA_PRIME1:
972 p = bn;
973 break;
974 case TAG_RSA_PRIME2:
975 q = bn;
976 break;
977 case TAG_RSA_EXPONENT1:
978 dmp1 = bn;
979 break;
980 case TAG_RSA_EXPONENT2:
981 dmq1 = bn;
982 break;
983 case TAG_RSA_COEFFICIENT:
984 iqmp = bn;
985 break;
986 }
987 }
988 }
989 dst__privstruct_free(&priv, mctx);
990 isc_safe_memwipe(&priv, sizeof(priv));
991
992 if (RSA_set0_key(rsa, n, e, d) == 0) {
993 if (n != NULL) BN_free(n);
994 if (e != NULL) BN_free(e);
995 if (d != NULL) BN_free(d);
996 }
997 if (RSA_set0_factors(rsa, p, q) == 0) {
998 if (p != NULL) BN_free(p);
999 if (q != NULL) BN_free(q);
1000 }
1001 if (RSA_set0_crt_params(rsa, dmp1, dmq1, iqmp) == 0) {
1002 if (dmp1 != NULL) BN_free(dmp1);
1003 if (dmq1 != NULL) BN_free(dmq1);
1004 if (iqmp != NULL) BN_free(iqmp);
1005 }
1006
1007 if (rsa_check(rsa, pubrsa) != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1008 DST_RET(DST_R_INVALIDPRIVATEKEY);
1009 if (BN_num_bits(e) > RSA_MAX_PUBEXP_BITS)
1010 DST_RET(ISC_R_RANGE);
1011 key->key_size = BN_num_bits(n);
1012 if (pubrsa != NULL)
1013 RSA_free(pubrsa);
1014 RSA_free(rsa);
1015
1016 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
1017
1018 err:
1019 if (pkey != NULL)
1020 EVP_PKEY_free(pkey);
1021 if (rsa != NULL)
1022 RSA_free(rsa);
1023 if (pubrsa != NULL)
1024 RSA_free(pubrsa);
1025 key->keydata.generic = NULL;
1026 dst__privstruct_free(&priv, mctx);
1027 isc_safe_memwipe(&priv, sizeof(priv));
1028 return (ret);
1029}

1031static isc_result_t
1032opensslrsa_fromlabel(dst_key_t *key, const char *engine, const char *label,
1033 const char *pin)
1034{
1035#if !defined(OPENSSL_NO_ENGINE)
1036 ENGINE *e = NULL;
1037 isc_result_t ret;
1038 EVP_PKEY *pkey = NULL;
1039 RSA *rsa = NULL, *pubrsa = NULL;
1040 char *colon, *tmpengine = NULL;
1041 const BIGNUM *ex = NULL;
1042
1043 UNUSED(pin);
1044
1045 if (engine == NULL) {
1046 if (strchr(label, ':') == NULL)
1047 DST_RET(DST_R_NOENGINE);
1048 tmpengine = isc_mem_strdup(key->mctx, label);
1049 if (tmpengine == NULL)
1050 DST_RET(ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
1051 colon = strchr(tmpengine, ':');
1052 INSIST(colon != NULL);
1053 *colon = '\0';
1054 }
1055 e = dst__openssl_getengine(engine);
1056 if (e == NULL)
1057 DST_RET(DST_R_NOENGINE);
1058 pkey = ENGINE_load_public_key(e, label, NULL, NULL);
1059 if (pkey != NULL) {
1060 pubrsa = EVP_PKEY_get1_RSA(pkey);
1061 EVP_PKEY_free(pkey);
1062 if (pubrsa == NULL)
1063 DST_RET(dst__openssl_toresult(DST_R_OPENSSLFAILURE));
1064 }
1065 pkey = ENGINE_load_private_key(e, label, NULL, NULL);
1066 if (pkey == NULL)
1067 DST_RET(dst__openssl_toresult2("ENGINE_load_private_key",
1068 ISC_R_NOTFOUND));
1069 if (tmpengine != NULL) {
1070 key->engine = tmpengine;
1071 tmpengine = NULL;
1072 } else {
1073 key->engine = isc_mem_strdup(key->mctx, engine);
1074 if (key->engine == NULL)
1075 DST_RET(ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
1076 }
1077 key->label = isc_mem_strdup(key->mctx, label);
1078 if (key->label == NULL)
1079 DST_RET(ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
1080 rsa = EVP_PKEY_get1_RSA(pkey);
1081 if (rsa == NULL)
1082 DST_RET(dst__openssl_toresult(DST_R_OPENSSLFAILURE));
1083 if (rsa_check(rsa, pubrsa) != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1084 DST_RET(DST_R_INVALIDPRIVATEKEY);
1085 RSA_get0_key(rsa, NULL, &ex, NULL);
1086 if (BN_num_bits(ex) > RSA_MAX_PUBEXP_BITS)
1087 DST_RET(ISC_R_RANGE);
1088 if (pubrsa != NULL)
1089 RSA_free(pubrsa);
1090 key->key_size = EVP_PKEY_bits(pkey);
1091 key->keydata.pkey = pkey;
1092 RSA_free(rsa);
1093 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
1094
1095 err:
1096 if (tmpengine != NULL)
1097 isc_mem_free(key->mctx, tmpengine);
1098 if (rsa != NULL)
1099 RSA_free(rsa);
1100 if (pubrsa != NULL)
1101 RSA_free(pubrsa);
1102 if (pkey != NULL)
1103 EVP_PKEY_free(pkey);
1104 return (ret);
1105#else
1106 UNUSED(key);
1107 UNUSED(engine);
1108 UNUSED(label);
1109 UNUSED(pin);
1110 return(DST_R_NOENGINE);
1111#endif
1112}
